<p>By Benozzo Gozzoli</p> 
<figure type="diagram"> 
<p>[DIAG HERE]</p> </figure> 
<p>A picture in the campo santo at Pisa of Noahs daughter looking at her drunken father, called the vergognosa di campo santo, proverbialy used for a mock modest<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The picture of Noah’s daughter is part of a fresco in the Camposanto Monumentale, a cemetery in Pisa, ‘The vintage and drunkenness of Noah’, painted by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5775.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Benozzo Gozzoli</ref> between 1469 and 1484. The figure appears at the far right of the fresco. ‘Vergognosa di campo santo’: the bashful girl of the holy field.</note>
        </div>        
            
